  "prompt": "Are pakistani girls allowed to wear skirt in public?",
  "response": "In Pakistan, the appropriateness of wearing skirts in public can vary significantly based on cultural, regional, and individual factors. In urban areas and more liberal environments, some girls and women do wear skirts and other Western-style clothing. However, in more conservative areas, wearing skirts may not be socially acceptable and could attract negative attention or disapproval.\n\nUltimately, personal choice plays a significant role, and many girls and women navigate their clothing choices based on their comfort, family values, and the social context of their surroundings. It's important to respect local customs and norms while also recognizing the diversity of experiences within the country.",
